Constant-rate birth death
========================================================

```{r}
tree <- pbtree(
  b = 0.2,
  d = 0.1,
  n = 10,
  extant.only = TRUE
)
```

```{r eval=FALSE}
plot.phylo(
  tree,
  edge.width = 1,
  cex = 2
)
```
***
```{r echo=FALSE}
library(ape)
plot.phylo(
  tree,
  edge.width = 1,
  cex = 2
)
```

Constant-rate birth death assumptions
========================================================

 * Instantaneous speciation (*Fennessy et al., 2016*)

![](fenessy_nubian_giraffe.jpg)

***

 * No co-occurence of speciation

![](fishes_in_lake.png)

Speciation takes time
========================================================

```{r echo=FALSE}
set.seed <- 42
library(becosys)
```

```{r}
pbd_tree <- bco_pbd_sim(
  create_pbd_params(
    erg = 0.2,
    eri = 0.2,
    scr = 0.01,
    sirg = 1.0,
    siri = 1.0
  ),
  crown_age = 2.0
)$igtree.extant
```

 * Protracted Birth-Death model

*Etienne & Rosindell, 2012*

***

```{r echo=FALSE}
phytools::plotSimmap(
  pbd_tree,
  colors = stats::setNames(c("gray","black"),c("i","g"))
)
ape::add.scale.bar()
```

Speciation can co-occur
========================================================

```{r echo=FALSE}
set.seed <- 42
library(mbd)
```

```{r}
mbd_tree <- bco_mbd_sim(
  create_mbd_params(
    lambda = 0.1,
    mu = 0.1,
    nu = 1.0,
    q = 0.5
  ),
  crown_age = 2.0
)$tes
```

 * Multiple Birth model
 * Laudanno et al., unpublished

***

```{r echo=FALSE}
ape::plot.phylo(mbd_tree)
```

What is the error we make today?
========================================================

 1. Create true tree
 2. Create DNA alignment
 3. Do Bayesian inference
 4. Compare posterior trees with true tree
 5. Does that error matter?


1. Create true tree
========================================================

```{r}
true_tree <- mbd_tree
```
```{r eval=FALSE}
plot.phylo(true_tree)
```
***
```{r echo=FALSE}
plot.phylo(true_tree)
```

2. Create DNA alignment
========================================================

```{r}
alignment <- sim_alignment(
  true_tree,
  sequence_length = 100,
  mutation_rate = 0.2
)
write.FASTA(alignment, "alignment.fas")
```

```{r eval=FALSE}
image(alignment)
```
***
```{r echo=FALSE}
image(alignment)
```

3. Do Bayesian inference
========================================================

```{r}
trees <- bbt_run(
  "alignment.fas",
  mcmc = mcmc
)$alignment_trees[51:100]
```

```{r eval=FALSE}
plot_densitree(
  trees,
  alpha = 0.1,
  width = 3,
  cex = 2
)
```
`
***
```{r echo=FALSE}
